WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:10.990 --> 00:00:16.049
I basically, in general, responded to the
building as a whole, particularly the exterior

00:00:16.049 --> 00:00:24.310
of the building, confronting the orange-ness
of the brick, and the horizontality of the

00:00:24.310 --> 00:00:32.189
pattern in the exterior of the building. The
amphitheater, as well, thatÕs a particular

00:00:32.189 --> 00:00:40.300
structure that I included in my design. Up
here, in fact, the way that I have the pattern

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:46.629
end, open, end and begin again in that particular
spot.

00:00:46.629 --> 00:00:54.190
I do the drawings by hand. I like that directness.
I like that approach. It becomes a kind of

00:00:54.190 --> 00:01:05.530
painterly exercise, in a way, just going through
this tactile, tangible process of mapping

00:01:05.530 --> 00:01:09.200
the design on the wall.

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:20.170
I love the power of design, pattern, and symbol
in traditional African art, and I learn from

00:01:20.170 --> 00:01:29.340
it quite a lotÑthe sense of invention, drawing,
the sense of space, material.

00:01:29.340 --> 00:01:33.909
You can do so many things with color and create
so many different situations, and I wanted

00:01:33.909 --> 00:01:38.429
to create ultimately a positive situation
here with the colors. I didnÕt want to have

00:01:38.429 --> 00:01:44.319
