depressive. I wanted thought provoking colors,

00:01:44.319 --> 00:01:50.890
interesting colors, interesting and dynamic
situations, environmental situations. When

00:01:50.890 --> 00:01:56.860
I make these kinds of installations, it seems
often enough that I deal with each wall as

00:01:56.860 --> 00:02:03.810
a separate event, and a circumstance or situation
based on how it exists, and then how it exists

00:02:03.810 --> 00:02:08.530
with the space adjacent to it. The first wall
was sort of like just the beginning of, letÕs

00:02:08.530 --> 00:02:14.160
say, a concert, where you have the big, loud
drums and the instruments tuning, and all

00:02:14.160 --> 00:02:19.500
thatÕs just [claps], just this CHH CHH CHH,
just this beginning. I call it Wall One, which

00:02:19.500 --> 00:02:25.651
is the entry wall at the door, and Wall Two,
which is the wall adjacent to itÉhow they

00:02:25.651 --> 00:02:32.490
meet at the corner and they fan out in this
kind of diagonal explosion. They just explode

00:02:32.490 --> 00:02:35.000
outward.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:41.030
I was thinking also of people traveling through
the spaceÑof the particular type of person

00:02:41.030 --> 00:02:46.640
